p: Related data also come from a cross-sectional study that was conducted in Thailand in 2016 during the rainy season, from May to October ( 10). The results identified 163 cases in 182 patients (89.56%) infected with DENV, with predominance of DENV-2. Among cases that were positive for DENV, coinfection with CHIKV was identified in 6 patients (3.68%) and coinfection with ZIKV was identified in one patient (0.61%).
